JOHANNESBURG - A 19-year-old student,Â Obed Leshoro, appeared in the Welkom Magistrate's Court on Thursday in connection with the murder of a 21-year old woman. The woman's burnt body was found in an open field in Dagbreek, Welkom. Her breasts had been cut off and a knife was stuck in her neck. Free State police spokesperson Captain Stephen Thakeng said Naledi Arcelia Lethoba, from Bothaville, was a student at Goldfields TVET College. He said her body was identified by her parents on Friday last week. The accused is a fellow student who was arrested at the college on Tuesday. The case against Leshoro was postponed to June 14 for a formal bail application. African News Agency (ANA)